- "sailors" refers to users;
- "set sail" is a metaphor for making requests;
- "vast ocean of active engagement" refers to the condition where the user status is 'active'.

- "Scholars" refer to users with non-administrator roles who are affiliated with universities;
- "Gatekeepers" represent users with the 'admin' role;
- "During the academic year of 2022" refers to the timeframe from January 1, 2022, to December 31, 2022;
- "Frequently visited" indicates the count of accesses to each article.

sql:
SELECT notification_type, notification_date
FROM notifications
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT title, page, section
FROM articles
WHERE author = 'AuthorFirstName AuthorLastName';

SELECT title
FROM newspapers
WHERE newspaper_id = 1;

SELECT newspapers.title AS newspaper_name, issues.issue_number AS chapter_number
FROM newspapers
JOIN issues ON newspapers.newspaper_id = issues.newspaper_id;

SELECT * 
FROM issues 
ORDER BY newspaper_id, issue_number;
